text.p: These are the leading stories in the Tunisian press on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

- Prime Minister Hamed Karoui, attending a meeting on youth and business, said 171 million dinars will be devoted to helping young people integrate into the economy within the 9th developement plan 1997-2001.
- Foreign Affairs Minister Abderrahim Zouari and visiting Egyptian counterpart Amr Moussa chaired on Thursday the two countries joint commission.
- Public Health Minister Hedi Mhenni on Thursday opened the first meeting aimed at reinforcing cooperation between African countries on family planning.
- New car ferry Ulysses of the Compagnie Tunisienne de Navigation (CTN) will make its first voyage on July 14.
